document_data.History:
Klevin was sent to Chult by the Lords' Alliance at the request of his father.{{Cite adventurers league/Putting the Dead to Rest|4}}

During the events of the [[death curse]] around {{Yearlink|1490}},{{ToA-time}} Klevin sought help from adventurers to investigate a smuggling ring operating out of [[Tiryki Anchorage]], which was run by [[Sanuya]], who was given a piece of the ''[[Dreamer's Amulet]]'' by [[Nahurali]].

After the death curse had ended and undead began assailing Port Nyanzaru, Klevin tasked his agents with finding anyone behind these attacks who could be brought to justice and&mdash;more importantly&mdash;be made to pay for the damage that had been caused.{{Cite adventurers league/Putting the Dead to Rest|5}} He also began to fear that [[yuan-ti]] had infiltrated his faction's ranks, and so sent an agent to the [[Tomb of Ihl]] to acquire the means to flush out the spies under the guise of investigating possible activity by cultists of [[Dendar]].{{Cite adventurers league/In Search of Secrets|17}}

When the [[Maze of Ubtao]] was found, Klevin had the idea to order one of his agents to dispose of an indestructible [[magic]]al [[dagger]] inside that [[dungeon]] so as that it could not be found and used to incriminate an ally of the Lords' Alliance, who had used it in a crime of passion.{{Cite adventurers league/Turn Back the Endless Night|3}}
